{
  "stem": "16214.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I understand, my-- my mother, after I was born in Krosniewice Ghetto, stayed with me there with my father and my grandparents for approximately five months until the end of the year.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from what I understand, when the Germans asked the Jews to pay 8 marks per head in order to be deported, my father felt that it was much better and much more safe for my mother to be in Warsaw Ghetto, since he just could not fathom that they could actually do the same thing so quickly as they did in Krosniewice Ghetto, and close down the ghetto, and get rid of all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he paid one of the ladies that he knew-- smugglers, basically-- who was able to smuggle my mother and myself to Warsaw Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was in the middle of the war, in the middle of the very, very hard winter, harsh winter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother got to Warsaw Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her sister-- one of her sisters-- I believe Irena-- was there, her older sister.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother moved in with-- with her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were several other people that were not related.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my aunt was living with her husband at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from what I understand, we-- we were living there for approximately seven months or so when everybody started saying to my mother that she should run away from there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my mother was basically waiting for my father, to hear from him, because he was supposed to run away from Krosniewice Ghetto to [?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Goleniow, ?] where his brother was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he wanted to actually prepare the documents in more safe place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is what exactly happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
